**Immediate Post-Treatment:**
- Continue gentle skincare for 2-3 months
- Gradually reintroduce products
- Oil production returns slowly
- Some dryness may persist weeks-months

**Skincare Reintroduction Timeline:**
| Time Post-Treatment | What You Can Add |
|---------------------|------------------|
| 0-1 month | Stick to gentle routine |
| 1-2 months | Vitamin C serum |
| 2-3 months | Gentle retinol (0.25%) |
| 3-6 months | Stronger retinoids, acids |
| 6+ months | Full active routine if desired |

**Relapse Statistics:**
- 20-30% relapse within 2 years
- More common: younger patients, truncal acne, lower cumulative dose
- Relapse is usually milder than original acne
- May need second course

**Preventing Relapse:**
- Maintain good skincare routine
- Consider low-dose retinoid maintenance
- Monitor hormonal factors
- Don't go back to old habits

**Scarring:**
Accutane helps prevent new scars but doesn't treat existing ones. Post-Accutane scar treatment options:
- Chemical peels (wait 6+ months)
- Microneedling (wait 6+ months)
- Laser resurfacing (wait 6+ months)
- Subcision
- Filler for ice-pick scars`,
